<document id="30843777"><sentence text="Assessment of drug-drug interactions between voriconazole and glucocorticoids."><entity charOffset="45-57" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s1.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="62-77" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s1.e1" text="glucocorticoids" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s1.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s1.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s1.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s1.e1" /></sentence><sentence text="Voriconazole is used to treat fungal infections in patients receiving glucocorticoid therapy in clinic"><entity charOffset="0-12" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s2.e0" text="Voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="70-84" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s2.e1" text="glucocorticoid" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s2.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s2.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s2.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s2.e1" /></sentence><sentence text=" The objective of this study was to characterize the potential drug-drug interactions (DDIs) between voriconazole and glucocorticoids using physiologically based pharmacokinetic (PBPK) models"><entity charOffset="101-113" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s3.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="118-133" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s3.e1" text="glucocorticoids" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s3.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s3.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s3.e1" /></sentence><sentence text=" Voriconazole and glucocorticoids PBPK models were constructed by using physicochemical data and pharmacokinetic parameters in healthy subjects, and verified by comparing the predicted pharmacokinetic parameters with corresponding data acquired from published literatures"><entity charOffset="1-13" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s4.e0" text="Voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="18-33" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s4.e1" text="glucocorticoids" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s4.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s4.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s4.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s4.e1" /></sentence><sentence text=" The refined PBPK models were employed to predict the potential DDIs between voriconazole and glucocorticoids"><entity charOffset="77-89" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s5.e0" text="voriconazole" /><entity charOffset="94-109" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s5.e1" text="glucocorticoids" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s5.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s5.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s5.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s5.e1" /></sentence><sentence text=" The results showed that the maximum plasma concentration (Cmax) and the area under the plasma concentration-time curve from 0 h to infinity (AUC0→inf) of dexamethasone were increased by 2"><entity charOffset="155-168" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s6.e0" text="dexamethasone" /></sentence><sentence text="44-fold and 2" /><sentence text="60-fold when combined with voriconazole, respectively"><entity charOffset="27-39" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s8.e0" text="voriconazole" /></sentence><sentence text=" For methylprednisolone, the Cmax and AUC0→inf were increased by 1"><entity charOffset="5-23" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s9.e0" text="methylprednisolone" /></sentence><sentence text="56-fold and 2" /><sentence text="23-fold, respectively" /><sentence text=" Our results indicate that the dose of dexamethasone or methylprednisolone can be reduced to maintain approximately similar exposures when used concomitantly with voriconazole"><entity charOffset="39-52" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e0" text="dexamethasone" /><entity charOffset="56-74" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e1" text="methylprednisolone" /><entity charOffset="163-175" id="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e2" text="voriconazole" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e0" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e0" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e2" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e1" /><pair ddi="false" e1="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e1" e2="DDI-PubMed.30843777.s12.e2" /></sentence><sentence text="" /></document>